	   <tr><td colspan=2>To be straight forward, this quest is tough.! Am i going to do it? Hell ya..! I always wanted the Soul Leech since i started playing my sk a year and a bit ago, but when i finally got it, i was disappointed, there are better weapons out there for sk's now, so it sits in my bank..The bad thing is doing this quest means you really need some uber peeps to group with, ie : an uber guild..I fortunately am in one but i feel for those who are not in one, perhaps not by choice. I know the game is geared towards people forming groups to obtain items and experience, but i did not think Verant would make it that everyone had to be in some huge guild of powerful people to complete these quests, it is disappointing to see that the quests are geared towards those who are in these guilds..As for the weapon itself, i think it is great, and if you disagree then just don't do it..As for myself i am looking forward to the quest and going through the pain of getting it done, but like i said i am in a guild who have the people who can help me do it and i feel for those who are not in a guild because they chose to guild with friends and play the game for the fun of it..I have met alot of people in the game who have helped me without me asking or without asking for anything in return and for this reason i offer my services to those who need it, give me a month to complete this quest (fingers crossed), after that just send me a tell and i will get one full party of 50+ peeps to help you (just make sure you can get 1 more groups of the same please)..  I have played almost every class in game and i can say Sk's are the most challengeing characters to play, for this reason i will not let them get me down, and i am and always will be proud to say i am a Shadow Knight !!!<br>We grow stronger, as the Knight grows Darker !<br>  Noirangel Heavnfalln..     E - Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
